The paper deals with information theory and communication networks, which are typical topics in the cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) sub-categories. The use of caching and prefetching techniques also suggests the cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) sub-category. The paper also involves optimization and coding techniques, which are relevant to the cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) sub-category. Finally, the paper deals with the fundamental limits of coded caching, which is a topic in the cs.CC (Computational Complexity) sub-category.
